title: For Sale:  1944 Winchester M1 Garand 30-06 - Seen lots of action during WWII
postcontent:
This rifle was issued to a good friend of mine during Marine boot camp. He fought with it in Korea, and took many enemy lives with it. It has many stories to tell. I'm not into old firearms, so I’m offering it to a collector.

It's a Winchester, 1944 M1 Garand. It's in beautiful condition. The rifle has always been well taken care of. The stock has been oiled regularly, and the metal conditioned with oil. There isn't a speck of rust anywhere on it. There are very few dings on the wood from diving from enemy fire in Korea, but other than that, it's a beaut! All of the numbers on all of the parts of the rifle match. It's not a franken-garand.

She hasn’t been fired in quite a while (20 + years) but has always been cleaned, and cared for. Ram a cleaning cloth through the barrel, and it comes out white every time.

I know what she’s worth, but I’ll try the (make me an offer) thing before I set a price.

I have several photos, and can send more if you're interested.
